title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt Sporter complete pre ban lower *mint*
postcontent:
Trade for slightly more beat up Preban lower or a couple hand guns
Cash price 1200 or BRO

Preban Colt sporter complete lower receiver *mint* includes offset front takedown screw adapter so you can attach any modern upper and the stock big pin incase you want to buy the original sporter upper for it. I will have a Date of Manufacture letter from Colt about a week.

For those confused about preban and why they are valuable. Here in the state of Massachusetts we have an assault weapons ban to contend with. If you have a newly manufactured rifle you can't have things like an flash hider , you have to have a muzzle break or compensator pined and welded on, you can't have a collapsible butt stock or bayonet lug but if the lower receiver was manufactured before 1994 it is grandfathered in and you can have all of those evil features that you can't have on a post ban rifle.

postcontent:
This is a 1984 23' Fleetwood Jamboree. It is in good cosmetic shape inside and out (especially for the year). It runs and drives good; the breaks work. The roof does not leak and has been triple-coated with a quality elastomeric roof sealant within the past year.

*The generator does work and will power the 'hotel', but it needs a new fuel pump. I can get it going with starter fluid, or by forcing fuel in. It's a simple fix, but I don't have a ton of time these days. I can show that it runs when you take a look.

*The water line was hooked straight up to the house (too much pressure) and cracked the incoming water line. This is another simple fix (cutting the cracked part and gluing in another section of pipe).

*The fridge does not work when plugged into the house. It probably works fine with propane still but the tank needs to be filled to find out. I think there is a wire short issue that is causing the problem.

*The AC, heater, stove, shower, toilet, lights, and outlets work.


It's a great roof over your head/place to stay when you're temporarily staying at the in-laws. It needs a few EASY fixes, but it worked fine for what I needed it for (a portable bedroom).

Come by and check it out.

title: For Sale:  Franchi SPAS 12 Semi Auto & Pump Action  12ga. Shotgun
postcontent:
For sale or trade is an excellent condition SPAS 12 semi-auto/pump action 12ga. shotgun, you don't see these come up everyday.  The finish looks really good all over, but of course there is some finish missing where you work the action from normal use.  Whether you want to feel like the Terminator or take on Velociraptors, this is the shotgun for any occasion, it's been used in hundreds of movies and video games.  From researching, there are about 1,800 SPAS 12 shotguns that made it into the U.S. before the ban, so I guess you could say it is somewhat rare.  This one has all of the must haves for a SPAS 12, it has the folding stock, the coss-bolt safety and the "hook", which is a carry handle that can be rotated for one handed shooting or taken off completely.  I had no intention of selling or trading this "any occasion tool", but I really want a SCAR 16 or 17 (FDE preferred,but not a must), so it's up on the block now!  I have seen these listed on Gunbroker and other classifed ads recently from $2,000-$3,000 on average, depending on condition etc., so this is what I have to go on for value, so I'll start at $2,000 obo. and see where it goes, will listen to reasonable all cash offers, so try me.  Message me for additional pics.

If wanting to trade, please state what you have and exactly what you want to do, straight trade, trade +/- cash, ammo, optics, etc. either way, so I know the deal.

Not in need of anything at all right now and really only wanting the SCAR right now, but I listed some I would not mind having or having more of since I know cash can be tight for folks, not limited to:

FN SCAR 16 or 17 
Vortex vmx-3t magnifiers in new to excellent condition 
Vepr 7.62x54 or .308 with barrel 20.5"-23", maybe another PSL

Colts 
FAL 308/7.62
AR-10 
Sig 556 or 556r piston models ( only the newer model with the upgrades and bugs worked out)
Will consider several quality stripped AR lowers. 
Beretta CX4 in 9mm with rails
AK-47 rifles like Norinco Mak-90, Arsenal or Saiga converted model or not converted, I can convert myself easily.
Saiga 12 unconverted, may consider other calibers too if unconverted or converted if a good deal.
Beretta 92FS INOX, Brigadier, M9A1, 92A1, M9 and 92FS in this order, these are some of my favorites 
Mossberg 930 SPX or 590A1, maybe 500 models.
XDM 5.25" or 4.5" in 9mm or .45ACP, will consider another XD Tactical 5" in .45ACP, bi-tone preferred. 
Quality higher powered optics in the 24x-32x range or similar for .300 Win Mag, .308 and .223 rifles.  A Nikon M-308 would be a good one. 
Eotech, maybe Aimpoint and descent magnifiers in the 3x-7x power, looking to finish off several rifle projects, so if you have multiples let me know.  Maybe 1-4x like the Burris set up with Fast Fire red dot on top, maybe the Burris MTAC 1.5-6x40mm or other 1-6x optics.
Maybe more revolvers, Ruger GP100 .357 mag. 4" or 6" or other .357 mag. models, will consider .357 mag lever action, .44 Mag revolvers, maybe lever too.
Bolt actions in .223/5.56 and .308/7.62x51 must be rated for both like Savage.  Maybe a .22 Mag rifle too.

Ammo in the popular calibers: .22lr, .22 mag., 9mm, .40 S&W, .45ACP, .357 mag., .44 mag., .223/5.56, 7.62x39,
.308/7.62x51, 7.62x54, .300 Win Mag., 12ga. in "00" & "000", same on ammo as firearms, I have plenty of everything, but I will consider more ammo to make a deal, depending on the value you place on the ammo.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Free floated AR15 brand new  wylde  target chamber
postcontent:
Up for sale is a free floated barrel Ar15 with m4 barrel with .223 wylde chamber(will also shoot 5.56) 1:9, PSA mil spec 7075 forged upper and lower, magpul moe pistol grip, trigger guard and mag. Brand new, never fired! Priced to sell at $750 


From Wiki: 
The .223 Wylde is a proprietary rifle cartridge chamber with the external dimensions and lead angle as found in the military 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and the 0.2240 inch freebore diameter as found in the civilian SAAMI .223 Remington cartridge. Rifles with a .223 Wylde chamber will typically accept both .223 Remington and externally slightly larger 5.56×45mm NATO ammunition.[1]

The .223 Wylde hybrid chamber was designed by Bill Wylde of Greenup, IL to exploit the accuracy advantages of the .223 Remington chambering without pressure problems or compromising the functional reliability of (semi) automatic weapons like the AR-15 family when using 5.56×45mm NATO military ammunition.[2] Coincidentally, it shoots the relatively long and heavy 80-grain (5.18 g) bullets commonly used in the sport of Highpower Rifle Competition very well and is one of the preferred chambers for that use. The Wylde chamber is used by a few rifle manufacturers who sell "National Match" configuration AR-15 rifles, barrels, and upper receivers.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Highly customized Saiga 12. taking offers or trades.
postcontent:
Last time I'm putting this up for awhile. Tired of being flagged for misunderstood reasons.

Up for grabs is my highly customized Saiga 12
Here are the specs and what it comes with.

The Saiga 12 to start features a dual recoil stock adapter tube and stock itself both from mako. Making recoil even with slugs minimal. Cheek riser is also on the stock. Moving up I have a chaos extended quad rail that goes all the way back over the dust cover. Great brand. On the quad rail we have an eotech 512 that also has customer made lens flip covers. Mbus gen 2 flip up sites. Klarus tactical 880 lumen light. Kryptonite k15 battle ready laser. As well as rail covers and a solid adjustable for end grip. The barrel shroud and muzzle brake combo was custom made and ordered through alumalite and features a brake that is perfect for this weapon. It was professionally converted by sniper co here in fort Wayne. Trigger guard. Mag release extension and safety extension all aftermarket. Comfortable pistol grip. Two sling pins. Now to move onto the internals. Everything was replaced or worked on. Trigger has been upgraded to match specs and polished. The entire bolt carrier and bolt were upgraded and polished. Tromix firing pin. Tom Cole op rod. All aftermarket gas adjusters and pics. Gas holes has been bored out to proper specs. The recoil system has been completely redone by jt engineering. Buffers and polishing galore. Also features the Pauly piston canted charging handle welded on in place of the original charger.

The wait time on the internals to get done took 9 months. The guy who did the work "glassbolt" best in the business according to the Saiga forums. Has closed his doors and is no longer offering his services.

On top of all that the entire gun was DURACOATED urban camo. All done by hand and took 3 weeks to completely paint and finish.

All the magazines 11 in total were also painted to match. Very expensive to duracoat everything in this design. I have one 20 round drum and a 12 round mag included. The rest are 10 rounders and one 5 rounder.

On top of all that I have 500 rounds of buck shot 00 and 4 to go with it all.
Two ammo cans. Very nice rifle case. And a blue filter for the light. Bandoliers and belts.

REDACTED

Let me know what cash offers or trades you may have.

FNX tactical is for sale or trade in another post.

Thank you for your time.
